M|Sect|tx|---
M|1. E|**Im|** ct
M|1. E|**De|** Waterfalls are the #1 perf killer. Each sequential await adds full network latency. Eliminating them yields the largest gains.
M|2. B|**Im|** ct
M|2. B|**De|** Reducing initial bundle size improves Time to Interactive and Largest Contentful Paint.
M|3. S|**Im|** hi
M|3. S|**De|** Optimizing server-side rendering and data fetching eliminates server-side waterfalls and reduces rp times.
M|4. C|**Im|** md-hi
M|4. C|**De|** Automatic deduplication and efficient data fetching patterns reduce redundant network requests.
M|5. R|**Im|** md
M|5. R|**De|** Reducing unnecessary re-renders minimizes wasted computation and improves UI responsiveness.
M|6. R|**Im|** md
M|6. R|**De|** Optimizing the rendering process reduces the work the browser needs to do.
M|7. J|**Im|** lo-md
M|7. J|**De|** Micro-optimizations for hot paths can add up to meaningful improvements.
M|8. A|**Im|** lo
